# JavaScript

## Overview
JavaScript is a programming language used to make web pages interactive. It runs in the browser and can also run outside the browser with environments like Node.js.

## What JavaScript Is Used For
- Making buttons, menus, and forms interactive
- Creating animations and dynamic content
- Working with APIs and server data
- Building full web applications
- Writing backend code with Node.js

## Basic Concepts
- Variables store data using `let`, `const`, or `var`.
- `const` is used when a value should not be reassigned.
- `let` is used when a value may change.
- Functions group code so it can be reused.
- JavaScript responds to events like clicks, typing, and page loading.

## Simple Example
```javascript
let language = "JavaScript";

function greet() {
  console.log("Hello from " + language);
}

greet();
```

## Why Learn It
JavaScript is one of the core technologies of the web, along with HTML and CSS. Learning it is important if you want to build modern websites and web apps.
